question: (Sarah of the Clue Crew delivers the clue from the Cleveland Clinic.)  Accessing these images on a computer so they're instant and expandable is a big innovation for the Cleveland Clinic. In 1929, when they were nitrocellulose, films stored here combusted, killing 123 people.
